  "description": "ORCA echolocation click train (28 Hz, resonance 0.95) fires into OPAL's granular engine via EnvToMorph coupling. OPAL's grain pitch follows ORCA's mod envelope arc. The sonar locates acoustic space; OPAL samples what the sonar found and holds it in granular suspension. Every ORCA note search generates an OPAL memory.",
